// saddle_escape.hexa — cross-domain discovery primitive (RTSC+NUCLEAR meta-domain §F6)
//
// Shared "instability -> deeper minimum" escape step. Both sibling discovery
// funnels reach an unstable extremum (saddle) and must step toward a stable
// basin before re-evaluating:
//   - RTSC (compositional): x = atomic positions, v = soft-mode eigenvector of
//     a negative-curvature phonon (e.g. H3As Im-3m Gamma-triplet -1243.69 cm-1)
//     -> displaced structure to vc-relax into the R3m-like minimum.
//   - NUCLEAR (elemental): x = (Z,N) point, v = gradient toward the nearest
//     shell-magic island (C2 island-of-stability weighting) -> drifted nuclide.
//
// The shared, computable core is a generic displacement: given a point x, an
// instability DIRECTION v, and a step magnitude delta (same units as x),
// return x' = x + delta * v. The instability direction's PHYSICS (how v is
// obtained: phonon eigenvector vs shell-gap gradient) and any normalization
// stay in the per-domain caller -- only the displacement vector op is shared.
//
// STATUS: stub-first (commons @D g60). The displacement core is implemented +
// deterministic; the domain eigenvector/gradient extraction is NOT here.
// R4: this proposes a CANDIDATE escape step only -- it asserts no stability,
// Tc, or half-life claim; absorbed=false semantics are unaffected.
// TODO: (1) optional in-kernel normalization helper (needs sqrt import);
//       (2) self-test sentinel per stdlib convention;
//       (3) atlas register once a closed-form verify path exists (cf. #1126).

// saddle_escape -- step point x[] along instability direction v[] by magnitude
// delta, returning the displaced point x'[]. Caller supplies v as the
// (optionally pre-normalized) direction. If len(v) != len(x), returns x
// unchanged (no escape proposed -- malformed direction).
pub fn saddle_escape(x: array, v: array, delta: float) -> array {
    let n = len(x)
    let mut out = []
    if len(v) != n {
        let mut j = 0
        while j < n { out.push(x[j]); j = j + 1 }
        return out
    }
    let mut i = 0
    while i < n {
        out.push(x[i] + delta * v[i])
        i = i + 1
    }
    return out
}
